vectorData.altText: That's right!  The eosinophilic staining cells located at the base of the intestinal glands are referred to as Paneth cells! They secrete antibacterial compounds, such as lysozyme.

This histological section of the ileum shows Paneth cells (PC) within the intestinal glands of the mucosa. These cells heavily stain with eosin which make them look reddish-pink.
